=== Phase A URL integration — manual smoke test log ===
Date:        2026-05-11
Branch:      phase2d-pyside6-migration
Commits:     (5 small commits: dialog UI, worker + queue wiring, progress
              dialog + cancel, this smoke log template, CHANGELOG entry)
Tester:      Junaid
Platform:    macOS, Python 3.14 venv (.venv/), PySide6==6.9.3
Surface:     auto_render.py only — cutter / merge / mixer untouched.

PURPOSE
   Confirm that Phase A integration:
     1. preserves the existing local-file render flow byte-for-byte,
     2. adds a working URL input path that ends up in the same render
        pipeline as a locally-picked file,
     3. handles cancel cleanly,
     4. shows a truthful summary of successes/failures.

INSTRUCTIONS
   Fill in the OUTCOME column with PASS / FAIL / NOT_TESTED. If any
   step FAILs, paste the error or describe what went wrong inline.
   Save the completed file. (ADR-0001 keeps smoke logs immutable
   once committed.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------
T1. App launches cleanly
----------------------------------------------------------------------
    source .venv/bin/activate
    python auto_render.py
    Verify: window opens, no traceback in terminal, no error popup.
    OUTCOME:   [   ]   notes:

----------------------------------------------------------------------
T2. EXISTING local-file flow still works (regression gate)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
    Click "📥 Select" -> pick a local .mp4
    Verify: file appears in tree with duration/resolution columns.
    Click "🗑️ Delete" on one row -> verify it's removed.
    Re-add the same file.
    Pick an encoder preset (any libx264 entry).
    Pick an output directory.
    Click "▶️ Start" -> wait for render.
    Verify: output .mp4 is in the chosen folder and PLAYS in a media player.
    OUTCOME:   [   ]   notes:

----------------------------------------------------------------------
T3. URL dialog opens, validates input gating
----------------------------------------------------------------------
    Click "🌐 Add URL".
    Verify: dialog opens with empty text area + quality combo (default
            "best") + subtitles checkbox (default off) + concurrent
            spin (default 3).
    Verify: OK button is DISABLED until at least one non-empty line
            is typed.
    Type a single URL. Verify: OK becomes enabled.
    Click Cancel. Verify: dialog closes, no other UI side-effects.
    OUTCOME:   [   ]   notes:

----------------------------------------------------------------------
T4. URL download (single short URL, "best" quality, no subtitles)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
    Click "🌐 Add URL".
    Paste one short, public, non-age-gated video URL (a Creative-
    Commons clip you control, or a known short public YouTube video).
    Quality = best, subtitles = off, max_concurrent = 3.
    Click OK.
    Verify: progress dialog appears with "Downloading 1/1: ... NN%".
    Verify: output panel logs "[URL 1] NN.N%  https://..." lines.
    Wait for completion.
    Verify: summary modal says "Downloaded 1/1 URL(s) successfully."
    Verify: downloaded file is in ~/.../url_downloads/ (platformdirs
            default; on Mac that's ~/Library/Application Support/1vmo/
            or similar — see core/user_data.py).
    Verify: file now appears in the tree_videos list with duration +
            resolution columns populated.
    OUTCOME:   [   ]   notes:

----------------------------------------------------------------------
T5. Downloaded file renders successfully through existing pipeline
----------------------------------------------------------------------
    With the downloaded file selected, pick an encoder preset.
    Click "▶️ Start".
    Verify: render runs identically to a local-file render.
    Verify: output .mp4 PLAYS in a media player.
    OUTCOME:   [   ]   notes:

----------------------------------------------------------------------
T6. URL download — cancel mid-batch
----------------------------------------------------------------------
    Click "🌐 Add URL".
    Paste 3 URLs (any mix).
    Click OK to start the batch.
    Within a few seconds, click "Cancel" on the progress dialog.
    Verify: progress dialog closes within ~10 seconds.
    Verify: summary modal lists which URL(s) succeeded vs which were
            cancelled (error_type = "cancelled").
    Verify: any partial in-flight files are left in url_downloads/
            (yt-dlp .part files are acceptable; not promoted into the
             render queue because .success=False for cancelled URLs).
    OUTCOME:   [   ]   notes:

----------------------------------------------------------------------
T7. URL download — invalid URL handling
----------------------------------------------------------------------
    Click "🌐 Add URL".
    Paste an obviously-invalid URL like "not a url" or
    "https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=...".
    Click OK.
    Verify: batch ends, summary lists the URL with error_type
            "invalid_url" (or similar).
    Verify: no crash; the rest of the UI still works.
    OUTCOME:   [   ]   notes:

