T10. URL download — close window during in-flight batch (Bug 2)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
    Added 2026-05-12 alongside the closeEvent URL-aware guard.
    Click "🌐 Add URL", paste 2-3 URLs, click OK.
    While the progress dialog is visible, click the main window's
    close (X) button.
    Verify: a confirmation modal appears: "A URL download is in
            progress. Cancel it and exit?"
    Click "No". Verify: the app stays open; the download keeps going.
    Click the close button again, this time "Yes".
    Verify: the worker is cancelled, the thread joins within ~5 s,
            and the app closes (does not hang or zombie). Any
            in-flight partial files in url_downloads/ are acceptable.
    OUTCOME:   [N]   notes: not run — added with the Bug 2 fix on
            2026-05-12; will be executed alongside T9 on the next
            Windows manual smoke pass. Marked [N] rather than [PASS]
            per the same rule cited under T9.

